         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">London ¶ 25, WILTON PLACE, S.W. ¶ Decr 21 1868 ¶ My dear Sir ¶  ¶ I send by this mail the remaining sheets of the 4th volume of the Flora Australiensis. The volume was published about ten days since a...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">68.12.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M4, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">London</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">25, WILTON PLACE, S.W.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Decr 21 1868</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I send by this mail the remaining sheets of the 4th volume of the Flora Australiensis. The volume was published about ten days since and the publishers inform me that the thirty copies for your Government were forwarded by the same channel as the previous ones I trust they will arrive safe</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A box has been sent per Somersetshire containing your specimens of <name key="Solaneae">Solaneae</name>
               <name key="Scrophularineae">Scrophularineae</name> and other remaining Orders included in the fourth volume.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I fear it will be some little time before I shall be able to begin upon the fifth volume. I am obliged to fulfil an old engagement with Martius to work up the Brazilian <name key="Caesalpinieae">Caesalpinieae</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham (</seg>1859-76), part 2, pp. 41-254, published 1 December 1870 (TL2).</p>
               </note> which he now presses for and this winter a severe attack of rheumatism has much interfered with my labours When I resume the Australian Flora the remaining gamopetalous Orders and the curvembryous <name key="Monochlamydeae">Monochlamydeae</name> will take me some time. These will be followed by <name key="Laurineae">Laurineae</name> which I suppose are but few — still I do not think I can come to the <name key="Proteaceae">Proteaceae</name> (which come next) till next winter</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am having the <name key="Hemiarrhena">Hemiarrhena</name> (your <name key="Vandellia%20plantaginea">Vandellia plantaginea</name>) figured for Hooker's Icones.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Hooker (1867-89), vol. 11, plate 1059 &amp; pp. 46-7. </p>
               </note> It is one of those provoking plants that interferes with all systematic arrangement</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope that if you have now a little more leisure since your great Exhibition is over you will take up your projected great work on <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name> — I perceive that Australian botanists are as little satisfied as I am with my classification of the genus and am very anxious to see your cortical system properly worked out for the whole genus — It was quite impossible to do that here from dried specimens even when accompanied by the collectors notes often so vague or contradictory.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I should naturally wish you at this season of the year a merry Christmas and a happy new year but that all that will be over long before this can reach you so that I can only wish you generally health and time to continue your valuable labours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours very sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Bentham</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr F. Mueller FRS</p>
